data.description:
Modern, newer, & very spacious townhouse for sale in Cypress Oaks.Built in 2017, this south-facing unit boasts 2,222 AC sq ft & 3,003 sq ft total. All impact windows & doors. A large, covered porch (24x9) with a ceiling fan faces an extensive park with sidewalks & abundant birds & trees. A 2-car garage (20x21) easily fits a midsize SUV & & sedan, the driveway fits 2 cars & there's plenty of guest parking around the unit.A 5-ton AC has been professionally maintained by Lindstrom. A French-door style refrigerator was added in 2023. The lower flooris 950 AC sq ft with beautiful porcelain tiles, 42'' cabinets in the kitchen & an extra-large island, dual sink, all granite countertops, & SS appliances. This open area that includes the kitchen, living and dining room is very large with high ceilings, 9 ft doors & a 1/2 bathroom. 

The upper floor is even larger at about 1,270 AC sq ft. A laundry room with an utility sink is conveniently located upstairs along with the easily accessible air handler. The loft (9x11) doubles as an office. 

There are 3 bedrooms upstairs. The master area is huge with a 25x20 bedroom, 10x10 walk-in closet, & a 10x10 master bathroom with dual sinks, separate deep tub & shower, & private toilet.

The second & third bedroom both have balconies. One is 15x10, the smaller is 12x11, sharing a full bathroom with a tub. 

The entire upstairs is covered in absolutely flawless, high-end carpet with extra padding. High ceilings & 9 ft doors make the space look even more spacious. The entire house is meticulously clean & well kept. 

The $330 monthly HOA fee covers reliable, high-speed internet (250 mbps+) & dozens of HD TV channels, roof & exterior maintenance, landscaping, a pool, gym and Clubhouse. The house has an alarm with 2 keypads. 

Utilities bills average $60 for water (high usage, fairly stable) & $110 for electric. For reference, HO insurance $3,100 this year, property taxes, $3,700 (homestead).

Cypress Oaks neighborhood is close to supermarkets, shopping, restaurants, parks, churches, major highways, & minutes from downtown, the beach, the airport and the equestrian world in Wellington. With very low availability in this great, newer neighborhood this townhouse won't last!
